# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SECURITY NOTE — EXPO_PUBLIC_* variables are embedded in the compiled app
# bundle and are readable by anyone who extracts it. Treat them as
# obfuscation helpers, not secrets.
#
# Real security lives on the server:
#   - put your OpenAI key in the proxy server's environment (never here for
#     store builds)
#   - validate EXPO_PUBLIC_ANALYZE_SECRET server-side as a lightweight
#     rate-limit guard, not for confidentiality
#   - enforce quotas and IP limits in the proxy
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Production: HTTPS analyze proxy (see ../cleanliving-api). Example:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_ANALYZE_API_URL=https://your-project.vercel.app/api/analyze

# Shared proxy guard — obfuscation/rate-limit only, not a real secret:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_ANALYZE_SECRET=optional-shared-secret-matching-server

# Dev-only: calls OpenAI directly from the device.
# NEVER set this for preview or production builds — use the proxy instead.
# The production EAS profile explicitly clears this variable (see eas.json).
# EXPO_PUBLIC_OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Amazon Associates tag for curated swap links (optional)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_AMAZON_ASSOCIATE_TAG=

# Impact.com (or any HTTPS tracking URL). When set, swaps in that bucket use Impact instead of Amazon.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_IMPACT_URL_SKINCARE=
# EXPO_PUBLIC_IMPACT_URL_SNACK=
# EXPO_PUBLIC_IMPACT_URL_HOME=
# EXPO_PUBLIC_IMPACT_URL_APPAREL=

# Sentry DSN for crash reporting (optional; safe to set in .env or EAS secrets)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=
